James Ritchie was forced to resign from his role as women's officer for the Tasmanian University Union . 
  He was voted into the job with a clear majority over a female candidate . 
  Public pressure and an online petition opposed the decision to employ a male for the job . 
  Mr Ritchie said he felt his ability to do the job was 'diminished' The position has no gender specified in the job description . 
 